name: Trump
summary:
**News Headlines Summary**

President Biden has asserted that he will no longer engage in debates, while tensions remain high after a shooting incident at a Trump rally in Pennsylvania that resulted in the death of a suspected gunman. Former President Trump claims to have been shot in the ear, but the accuracy of this account is disputed. Analyst J.D. Vance faces criticism, and a debate has emerged over the future of the "Never Trump" movement. Texas leaders have condemned the assassination attempt on Trump, while a poll indicates Trump's lead over Biden amid concerns about Biden's mental fitness.
